## Architecture

{{#each stacks}}
{{#if (eq this "nestjs")}}
### NestJS Architecture

This is a NestJS application following the modular architecture pattern.

**Key Directories:**
- `src/` - Source code
- `src/modules/` - Feature modules
- `src/common/` - Shared utilities
- `test/` - Unit and e2e tests

**Common Commands:**
```bash
npm run start:dev    # Development with watch mode
npm run test         # Unit tests
npm run test:e2e     # End-to-end tests
```
{{/if}}

{{#if (eq this "express")}}
### Express.js Architecture

This is an Express.js application with a lightweight server architecture.

**Key Directories:**
- `src/` - Source code
- `src/routes/` - Route handlers
- `src/middleware/` - Custom middleware
- `src/controllers/` - Business logic

**Common Middleware:**
- `body-parser` - Request body parsing
- `cors` - Cross-Origin Resource Sharing
- `morgan` - HTTP request logging
{{/if}}

{{#if (eq this "nextjs")}}
### Next.js Architecture

This is a Next.js application with React for building web applications.

**Key Directories:**
- `app/` or `pages/` - Routes and pages
- `components/` - React components
- `public/` - Static assets
- `styles/` - CSS/styling files

**Common Commands:**
```bash
npm run dev       # Development server on port 3000
npm run build     # Production build
npm run start     # Start production server
```
{{/if}}

{{/each}}

